<section class="block-section story">
  <span class="section-tag">📖 Story</span>
  <h2>Why this block matters</h2>
  <p class="sub">The course's central question: <em>How do you live well on a changing Earth?</em></p>
  <p>Before we get into plate tectonics, climate, water, or anything else, we have to agree on how we work in this class. That means three things: how we treat sources, how we use AI, and how we make claims with evidence. Today is the start of the first one.</p>
  <p>The anchor skill for the whole year is <strong>OPVL</strong> — Origin / Purpose / Value / Limitations. It's the framework you'll apply to every paper, news article, government report, and AI output we touch this year. We learn it here, in low stakes, and come back to it in every subsequent unit at increasing difficulty.</p>
</section>

